The paper deals with a problem of assigning tasks to a swarm of agents, which is a typical problem in multi-agent systems. Therefore, cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a linear programming approach to solve the problem, which involves optimization and control of the agents, making cs.RO (Robotics) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of cost metrics and the consideration of dynamics, which are topics in machine learning and optimization, respectively, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a theoretical justification for the approach based on optimal transport theory, which is a topic in mathematics and optimization, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category as well.
